Two multivariate analyses were performed, one for each outcome of interest (ARDS and death). In the first model, the characteristics found to be associated with the risk of ARDS were history of ischemic heart disease (OR 7.5 (95%CI 1.6-36.2), p=0.04), fever at disease diagnosis (OR 17 (95%CI 4.5-64), p=0.0009), age at symptoms onset (OR 1.1 (95%CI 1-1.15), p=0.03) and shortness of breath at disease onset (OR 20, (95%CI 3.6-79.3), p=0.004). In the second model, the characteristics associated with the risk of death were fever at disease diagnosis (OR 18.7 (95%CI 2.4-146), p=0.02), cough at disease diagnosis (OR 4 (95%CI 1.02-17.6), p=0.05) and higher serum CRP at disease diagnosis (OR 5.6 (95%CI 1.6-23.5), p=0.01) (
Table 3, Table 4
).
